✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Good level of difficulty for a Clash; I could solve it in under 5 minutes in JavaScript.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: The logic isn't far-fetched and can be easily spotted with the test cases
The required solution isn't a simple formula, but doesn't require very advanced techniques, so the solution can be rapidly written

In short: Nice clash

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: clever clash
I hope you received enough feedback from the community to improve your contribution. Once you have made the necessary updates, publish your contribution!
It was easy for me to spot the logic. Coding this was fun too.

This took way longer than I'd care to admit.
After looking at Stef's clash, I was way over complicating it. I had so many running theories, and even came to the conclusion that the last digit of the output was B*D's last digit. Which is technically true, but only because the 10s place won't effect the ones.


I actually think this would make a good clash. Made me feel silly.

Interesting clash!

Just one thing: i think you added an extra line at the bottom of "Random Set 1" and "Validator 3", which could be troublesome for people that read the whole input instead of just the n lines you provide with the first number. Is this intended?

Thanks :)
I like the way you format the text. because of a recent clash I was focused on the individual interpretation of the numbers. Interesting
Thanks for pointing that out. The extra lines have been removed
